    "Liquid nitrogen is often selected as a working fluid because, even if its thermophysical properties do not represent liquid hydrogen and oxygen perfectly, it is a first step towards thermodynamic similarity and an experimental cryogenic environment with respect to using classic laboratory fluids, e.g. alcohols.",
